Companion NOTICE file for generator-output artefacts under
grammars/treesitter/.

Six files under this directory are either generated by
`tree-sitter generate` or are third-party content vendored by
the same step, and lack a per-file SPDX header for the reasons
below:

  - src/parser.c                  (tree-sitter generator output)
  - src/grammar.json              (tree-sitter generator output)
  - src/node-types.json           (tree-sitter generator output)
  - src/tree_sitter/alloc.h       (tree-sitter ABI header; upstream content)
  - src/tree_sitter/array.h       (tree-sitter ABI header; upstream content)
  - src/tree_sitter/parser.h      (tree-sitter ABI header; upstream content)
  - package-lock.json             (npm-generated dependency lock)

(The first three are tree-sitter 0.22's canonical generator
output paths; the `src/tree_sitter/*.h` headers are bundled
verbatim from upstream `tree-sitter` for downstream C/wasm
consumers and follow the upstream tree-sitter MIT-licensed
ABI header convention — they are not project-authored.)

These artefacts inherit the project license (Apache-2.0 WITH
LLVM-exception) via this NOTICE file. The hand-authored sources
that drive their generation — `grammar.js`,
`queries/highlights.scm`, and `scripts/templates/grammar.js.template`
combined with `scripts/gen_treesitter_grammar.py` — DO carry
per-file SPDX headers in line-1 comment syntax appropriate to
each file format (`//` for grammar.js, `;` for highlights.scm,
`#` for the Python generator).

Rationale for the NOTICE pattern (per
specs/010-t8-tree-sitter-grammar/research.md §9):

  1. The upstream `tree-sitter` CLI's output emits no
     provision for custom file headers. Patching the CLI to
     inject SPDX headers would be a brittle upstream-fork
     burden; every CLI bump risks re-breaking the patch.

  2. Manually editing `parser.c` post-generation would break
     the regenerate-and-diff CI gate (FR-017 in spec.md).

  3. JSON has no comment syntax. The `_comment_top` JSON-key
     convention used elsewhere in this repo
     (.github/branch-protection.json,
     test/tooling/textmate/package.json) is not safe for
     `grammar.json`/`node-types.json` because tree-sitter
     downstream consumers (tree-sitter-graph, query authoring
     tools) may strict-validate the JSON shape and reject
     unknown top-level keys.

The exempted paths are listed explicitly in
scripts/spdx_exceptions.txt; scripts/check_spdx.py treats them
as EXEMPT and skips header validation. Adding any new
generated artefact under grammars/treesitter/ requires both an
update to scripts/spdx_exceptions.txt and a new entry in this
NOTICE file with the same rationale chain.

